Cycle detection in Directed graph using DFS = on the same path node has to be visited again.

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

WORD LADDER : BFS, Queue,set.

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

terminal nodes = no outgoing edges
safe nodes = anything that leads to terminal node is safe node

--> Any node part of cycle or connected to cycle (incoming edge to cycle from 
node where as outgoing edge from cycle can be safe node) can never be safe nodes.



////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

DIJKSTRA ALGO - priority queue,distance array,while loop.

SHORTEST PATH - store the parent node in the array(memoize) and follow DIJKSTRA algo.

1.doesn't work with negative weights
2.doesn't work with negative cycle

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

BELLMAN FORD ALGO - can find the shortest path for negative edges as well.

works only with directed graph.If given undirected graph make directed by adding two edges like 1 - 2 then make it as 1 -> 2 and 1 <- 2.
Relax all the edges N-1 times sequentially.
edges cam be in any order.

** Since is the graph is of N nodes, in worst case , we will take N-1 edges to reach from the first to last.thereby N-1 iterations.

Relaxation :- if(dist[u] + edw < dist[v]) dist[v] = dist[u] + edw;

on Nth iteration the relaxation will be done and if the dist[] array gets reduced then there exists negative cycle.

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FLOYD WARSHAL ALGO - multi source shortes path

finds shortest path from each node to all other nodes.
Also can detect negative cycles
note : Go via every vertex and node
Pre computed 
Dynamic Programming

for via =0;via<n;via++{
    for i=0;i<n;i++{
    for j=0;j<n;j++{
        cost[i][j] = min (cost[i][j] , cost[i][via] + cost[via][j]);
    }
}
}

detect a negative cycle :
 for(i to n){
    cost[i][j] < 0; it is negative
 }


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Minimum spanning tree 

-> A tree in which we are having N nodes and N-1 edges is called MST & all nodes are reachable from each other
-> a tree can have many spanning trees but tree with minimum weight is MST.

PRIM'S ALGO 

-- helps us to get minimum sum of MST and also its edges.
-- we need PQ(wt,node,parent), visited array

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Disjoint set DS 

-> Dynamic Programming
-> find parent -- if the ultimate parent of the two are same then they belong to same group
-> union - rank,size
-> rank = parent and rank array

Union (u,v)
1.find ultimate parent of u & v ; pu,pv
2. find rank of pu,pv
3. find smaller rank to larger rank always.

-- do path compression

