///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

KOSARAJU'S ALGO

-- Strongly connected components (SCC)
-- this also gives us number of SCC and print the SCC
-- SCC are only valid for directed graphs
-- if the pair of vertices are reachable vice-versa then the component is SCC.
-- thought process is reverse the edges and do dfs.
-- 1. sort all the edges according to finishing time.
-- 2. reverse the graph 
-- 3. do a dfs


///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

TARJAN'S ALGO

If after removing any of the edge, the graph is divided into two/more seperate graphs then that edge is called bridge.

-- two arrays 1. Time insertion array 2. low time insertion array
-- timeInsertionArray[] = DFS time insertion
-- lowestTimeInsertion[] =  min lowest time insertion of all the adjNodes expect parent node.
using the above two arrays based on the cond we can get the bridges.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

ARTICULATION POINT

-- Nodes on whose removal the graph breaks into multiple components

same as Tarjan's algo but slight diff in lowestTimeInsertion[] -- min of all adj nodes apart from parent & visited nodes




